  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-31 03:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] P&L Forensics: Share Truncation + Missing 8th Trade\n\n**Task:** Investigate $38 gap between expected and actual Day 1 P&L.\n\n**Finding 1: 8 trades, not 7!** There was a TRIPLE-trade at 11:38-11:39 (before double-fix). The 3rd trade ($12.15 @ 0.490) has NO outcome logged \u2014 its outcome check may have been lost when bot was killed at 11:39.\n\n**Finding 2: Integer share truncation**\n`quantity = int(size_usd / max_price)` \u2014 shares truncated to integers.\n- $11.07 at $0.484 = 22.87 \u2192 **22 shares** (actual cost $10.65, not $11.07)\n- Each trade leaves $0.40-0.90 unspent but the log reports the intended size\n- Over 8 trades: ~$5.20 in phantom spend that never actually happened\n\n**Finding 3: Fill price is target, not actual**\n`entry_price = result.get('price', target_price)` \u2014 falls back to target price. The CLOB may fill at a WORSE price than logged.\n\n**Root cause of $38 gap: combination of**\n1. Integer truncation (~$5 less spent than logged)\n2. Unknown fill prices (could be worse than target)\n3. Missing 8th trade outcome (lost $12.15 if it lost)\n4. PM taker fees (~2% on $94 = ~$1.88)\n5. The 8th trade itself \u2014 not accounted in outcomes JSONL\n\n**V5 TODO:** Log actual shares purchased and actual fill price from CLOB response. Currently we're flying blind on execution quality.\n\n## 2026-03-31 03:12 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] PM Settlement Resolved: $921.75 IS Correct Balance\n\n**Task:** Investigate PM settlement. Check redeem cron.\n\n**Finding:** The auto-redeem cron (`redeem-cron.",
